Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_schematic_add_selected(25.10)            gui_schematic_add_selected(25.10)

Name
       gui_schematic_add_selected - Adds the selected object to the current or
       specified schematic view

Syntax
       gui_schematic_add_selected

       [-help]

       [-name <window_name>]

       Adds the selected object to the current or specified schematic view.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description  of the gui_schematic_add_selected
              command.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man  command:
              man gui_schematic_add_selected.

       -name <window_name>
              Specifies  the  unique window name for an open schematic view to
              which the selected object needs to be added.

Related Information
              * gui_get_schematic

              * gui_schematic_load_view

              * gui_schematic_save_view

